Description:
Bigger & Better
Located in a highly sought after pocket with Drysdale Reserve, McLeods Waterholes and Drysdale shopping just a stroll away, this grand home is a cut above the rest. High ceilings, grand entrance, flowing open plan living spaces and a quality finish, coupled with a 1900 square meter block, brilliant shedding and alfresco entertaining with bar; this home really will appeal to those looking for something bigger and better. Comprising 3 large bedrooms, formal lounge, informal open plan family/dining room and a large billiards room flowing onto the outdoor entertaining. The home comes with a 4th bedroom or home office with a separate entrance & powder room, perfect for the extended family member or at-home consulting for the entrepreneur. Privacy, tranquillity and convenience can be expected from this quality home in a premier location.

Description:
Charm, Character & Tranquility on 1334sqm
This charming home sitting on a massive 1300sqm presents the opportunity to enjoy the space of a rural property combined with the convenience of being positioned right in the heart of Drysdale.
The original cottage dates back to 1873, possessing so much of its original character and has been blended with a more recent extension, resulting in a modern and substantial size home boasting 5 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms. The master bedroom with its own ensuite, the second bathroom is positioned to service the remaining 4 bedrooms with the flexibility to transform one into a study. These rooms are oversized and sit within the original cottage.
Offering two separate living zones. The formal lounge is adjacent to the master suite with its own private deck. You will enter into the huge family living and dining area flowing through French doors out to a massive entertaining deck stretching the length of the home. The country-style kitchen is central and well equipped with all mod cons (including Bosch dishwasher, Savoir-Faire 900mm oven, gas cooktop and range hood).
Step down to the private patio leading you into the impressive man cave boasting a concrete floor, wood burner, pizza oven and bar. Also staging as additional entertaining space when needed. Surrounding is a tranquil garden with plenty of backyard for the kids.
Extras include: Single carport, ducted heating, split system A/C and ample storage space.
You are certain to be impressed by this spacious and character filled property that will secure your families future for many years while enjoy a fruitful lifestyle. Inspection is a must!

Only 1 block remaining!
These newly subdivided, inner-Drysdale allotments boast huge proportions and present as a rare opportunity to build a large family home just a hop step and jump from all amenities. Within walking distance of Drysdale's central shopping precinct, parks, schools and sporting facilities. Set in the heart of the Bellarine Peninsula, renowned for it's beaches, cafe culture, wineries and breathtaking coastal scenery. Please note house is not for sale.
The location boasts an established atmosphere unlike that of the new edge-of-town subdivisions, and the size of the blocks is beyond compare! Each allotment comes complete with perimeter fencing.
Build your dream home! Capitalise on the space, convenience and potential of these large and desirable allotments.
25 minutes to Geelong, 90 minutes to Melbourne. Close to public transport.
Enquire without delay!

- Established atmosphere with new perimeter fencing
- Set in the heart of the Bellarine Peninsula
- 25' to Geelong, 90' to Melbourne
- House is not for sale

Description:
Life on the Rail Trail
AMENDED SALE DETAILS: Please note the land being sold is 948 sqm with information of acquiring the defunct section of Whistle Stop Lane at the rear. Imagine living with The Bellarine Railway Line at your back door. This is location living with direct access to the Rail Trail, Lake Lorne & the Drysdale Pony Club. This is a rare opportunity to acquire land with improvements to build on or just escape for the weekend in this unique location. You can ride or walk the Rail Trail all the way to Queenscliff or West to Geelong. Imagine the excitement of having historic steam & diesel trains pass by your back door or catching one to Queenscliff for the day or go that bit further via the Sorrento Ferry Service.
Offering 948 sqm of land with a 6 metre driveway, with the option to acquire the defunct Whistle Stop Lane at the rear subject to regulatory process (Information on this process available on request)
The self contained cabin offers two generous bedrooms.
Lounge room with split system airconditioner.
Galley style kitchen.
The cabin would ideally suit those looking to build their dream home with a rural & rail outlook or a weekend getaway backing onto the Rail Trail.
The driveway is to be gravelled to the shed.
Underground power & water is available at the street & would need to be connected to the cabin & shed.
Just a short commute to the town centre of Drysdale or Geelong & Ocean Grove. Walk or ride to the Bellarine Secondary, St Ignatius College & the new sporting precinct under construction.

Live along the creek line

The Central Walk Estate is within easy walking distance to the main street, with cafes, local butchers, Woolworths, Aldi & restaurants. Central Walk Estate is conveniently located within riding distance to St Ignatius College, Bellarine Secondary, Christian College & easy commute to Geelong.

Description:
I'VE FOUND PARADISE
In a quiet street close to the Drysdale Township, I have found paradise. This home secluded behind trees is a beautiful storybook style cottage. All you hear behind the gate are birds and the rustle of the trees. Timber and stone combine to bring this home together. Cosy up in the lounge with the wood heater in winter or chill out inside in summer with the protection of the verandas. Surrounded by a lovely garden and an orchard of trees that are watered through a reticulated system. Many a family gathering has been held here and many memories made. Is it your turn to make memories of your own? Drysdale is a historic town founded in the mid 1800â??s and you can still evidence of that era with our local steam train. Donâ??t let that fool you though because our town has all the modern amenities that we need to live today such as supermarkets, shopping centres, medical centres and schools. Add to this the choices of restaurants, cafes and bistros. Not to be outdone we also have an array of sporting options and recreation selections.

Ease of Living
Clean contemporary lines coupled with large family and sleeping quarters makes this just over 3 year old home built for comfort and ease of living, a delight to inspect. Family friendly with light and spacious rooms, perfectly zoned over a single level for the large growing family unit including light-filled open plan kitchen, dining and family room opening to an outdoor entertaining terrace, alfresco dining area and the landscaped garden. Located in one of the most central and sought after estates in 3222 on just over 600 sqm of land, this is the perfect family seaside haven.

Description:
Large Block, Lifestyle Location, Family Home
Located in a sought after pocket of the rural township of Drysdale, this lovely four bedroom family home sits in close proximity to the Bellarine Rail Trail and the historic Drysdale Railway Station. A relaxed lifestyle is on offer in this modern home. On entry the generous main bedroom complimented by a spacious ensuite and WIR is situated at the front of the home. Get the family together in the spacious open plan living area, expansive kitchen with walk-in pantry and 900cm free standing cooker. There is dual access from the living area to the vast outdoor deck. Perfect for entertaining all year round.
The minor bedrooms are all of generous proportions and serviced by the family bathroom located in a separate wing of the home. All bedrooms have ceiling fans and BIRs.
The gardens and outdoor living areas will delight - flourishing vegetable garden, room for the chooks and a cute cubby house with a back lawn manicured to the standard of any putting green.
Positioned on an expansive 778m2 block in close proximity to the township and local schools.
Inspection is a must to appreciate this lovely home.

Description:
Position Plus for This Substantial Family Home on 1280m2
Built in 1990 and constructed of man-made Hooblerstone this extensive home has everything the growing family requires including real estate's premium requirement of POSITION. Located in the centre of Drysdale and within walking distance to the shopping precinct, local kindergartens and schools, medical practitioners and numerous sporting arenas. Perfectly manicured gardens frame the entrance to this surprising property as you step inside the front gate.
The main entry to the home opens to living and bedroom wings. The formal lounge is spacious and framed by full length windows which provide perfect viewing for all that transpires along the street front. Open plan living at its premium incorporates the dining room which overlooks the games room and pool area and adjacent private study.
The heart of this home is its fabulous renovated kitchen with extensive preparation areas, storage a plenty, walk-in pantry, Bosch pyrolise electric wall oven, gas hotplates, Miele glass exhaust fan and beautiful Wautharong glass splashbacks. Family time can be spent in this area of the home where dining, TV and games can be pursued.
There are five bedrooms for family and friends. The main bedroom is at the front of the home with lovely bay window, spacious WIR and ensuite with double shower. The minor bedrooms with BIRs are serviced by a lovely family bathroom with separate toilet. The laundry is spacious and light - filled.
Extensive features of this home include fully insulated walls and ceiling, gas ducted under-floor heating, over-size ensuite, gas log fire, solar panels, Wautharong glass features, ceiling fans, air conditioners, solar and gas heated salt-chlorinated pool and spa, massive man-cave, extensive shedding, four water tanks, over-height garage roller doors with rear yard access, outdoor Coonara heater and built in barbeque the list goes on and on.
Recently installed to maximise power usage efficiency 20 Black Max Solar panels with a 5 Kw inverter.
This home must be inspected to be fully appreciated. Contact the agent for inspection now.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609
